# Implementation Plan - Advanced Settings, Dashboard Real Data, and Interactive Documentation

This implementation plan details the proposed updates to ensure real-time robust data loading on the admin dashboard, implement advanced app settings, and introduce a comprehensive admin documentation page.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Robust Data Fetching & Dashboard Real Data
To fix potential timestamp mismatches and query caching, we will make the client-side Firebase timestamp parsing more resilient and adjust the cache settings.

#### [MODIFY] [firebase-api.ts](file:///c:/Users/PC/Fia-Cbt-main/fgsigbohocbtv1/client/src/lib/firebase-api.ts)
- Update `docToData` to convert date fields and Firestore Timestamps robustly. If `data[key]` has a `.toDate()` function, call it; if it is an object with `seconds` and `nanoseconds`, construct a `Date` object from `seconds * 1000`.

#### [MODIFY] [queryClient.ts](file:///c:/Users/PC/Fia-Cbt-main/fgsigbohocbtv1/client/src/lib/queryClient.ts)
- Modify the default query client options. Replace `staleTime: Infinity` with a shorter stale time of 10 seconds (`staleTime: 10000`) and set `refetchOnWindowFocus: true`. This ensures the Admin Dashboard fetches real, fresh data from Firestore when the administrator loads the tab or focuses the browser window.

